combine

public java.util.List<Plan> combine(java.util.List<Plan> listA,
                                    java.util.List<Plan> listB)
Creates a list of plans as a result of the combination of two lists. Given a list of plans A: [[1, 2], [3, 4]] and a list of plans B: [[5, 6], [7, 8]] it returns a list contaning 4 plans: [[1, 2, 5, 6], [1, 2, 7, 8], [3, 4, 5, 6], [3, 4, 7, 8]]

Parameters:
listA -
listB -
Returns:
list combining listA and listB
